Bitwise Operations
------------------

Review Boolean

if x<10 and x>2:
    prin("foo")  <--- runs

if x<10 or x>2:
    prin("foo")  <--- runs


TRUTH TABLE
A   B    A AND B
-----------------
F   F        F
T   F        F
F   T        F
T   T        T 

TRUTH TABLE
A   B    A or B
-----------------
F   F        F
T   F        T
F   T        T
T   T        T 


Bitwise:

A   B    A & B
-----------------
0   0        0
1   0        0
0   1        0
1   1        1 

TRUTH TABLE
A   B    A | B
-----------------
0   0        0
1   0        1
0   1        1
1   1        1 

  11001100
& 11110000  AND Mask
-----------
  11000000

0b11111111 =255

255.255.255.0


In general:
* You can use AND to clear set to 0 Bits
* You can use OR to set (set to 1 ) Bits

Shifting
-------

Moving all bits in a number left or right

111001
011100
001110
000111

AND Mask
   123456789
d& 009900000 First AND
------------
   003400000 Then Shift 
   00034

